Moelis Hires Former Skadden Buyout Lawyer Saggese as Adviser

-- B y   Z a c h a r y   R .   M i d e r
-- 
2011-03-10T16:18:58Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-10/moelis-hires-former-skadden-buyout-lawyer-saggese-as-adviser.html
Moelis & Co., the four-year-old
investment bank founded by Kenneth Moelis, hired Nick Saggese, a
former lawyer at Skadden, Arps, Slate, Meagher & Flom LLP who
focused on private-equity deals and restructurings.  Saggese, 63, will be a senior adviser in  Los Angeles ,
counseling Moelis bankers and their clients, the New York-based
company said in a statement today. Saggese worked at Skadden for
25 years and retired as co-head of the firm’s private-equity
group.  Saggese advised  Paul Allen ’s Vulcan Capital on the sale of
Dreamworks SKG to Viacom Inc. in 2006, and Leonard Green &
Partners LP and TPG Capital on their acquisition of Petco Animal
Supplies Inc. that year. He co-wrote a leading handbook on
corporate restructurings, Moelis said.  Moelis, founded in 2007, has more than 470 employees in 7
offices around the world.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Zachary R. Mider in New York at 
